place_info.title: Cafe Graffiti
place_info.address: 8-2-672, 1/A, Rd Number 13, Mithila Nagar, Banjara Hills, Hyderabad, Telangana 500034, India

reviews.snippet:
One of the oldest cafes of banjara hills located at road number 13.

Affordable prices with good quality & quantity of food.

We tried the following items,

Chicken Alfredo Pasta 7/10
Broasted Chicken 9/10
Chicken Cheese Mutabbaq 9/10
Egg Mutabbaq 9/10
Meat Mutabbaq 10/10
Special Meat Burger 7/10
Chicken Zinger Burger 9/10
Chicken Zinger Wrap 10/10
Meat Sheekh Kebab 9/10
Mocktails 9/10 ( Green Apple recommended )
Chocolate Milkshake 8/10
Blackcurrant Milkshake 10/10 ( Highly recommended )
Iced Latte Hazelnut 6/10
Chocolate Donuts 10/10

They aren't serving naans anymore.

reviews.snippet:
One of my favourite restraunts in banjara hills! Whenever I'm low on cash,and I want to eat some good tasting food,this is where I go.
The staff members are super friendly.
They always suggest the best dish when you don't feel like deciding on your own.
I have went to this restraunt dozens of times,and I've never been disappointed.
There's even a dedicated family section on the first floor,which ofcourse is wayy better than the ground floor for bachelors.
The prices are quite reasonable.
Infact,I have found this place to be much cheaper than other restaurants with similar menus.

reviews.snippet:
Best place for Burgers and pasta.
I tried zinger burger and beef burger here. Hands down it is the best. Also try their potato wedges.
The burgers are full of flavour and spice.
And the interior is too minimalistic.
Love this place.
Also the food here is HALAL.
Good spot for a lunch date.
Shakes here are also good.
P.s Way better than sound cheesy

reviews.snippet:
Great little affordable place offering good some very delicious burgers, fries and Mojitos.
The beef burgers are some of the bestt in the cityy. The zinger burgers are a little dry though. Apart from that it’s a cozy place offering good ambience, a neat setup and a relaxing quite time.
The place has gotten much larger after their recent renovation, and prices are still pretty affordable so that’s something really nice.
Service is quick and appropriate.
Overall 8/10.

reviews.snippet:
I had discovered the place a few years ago and it's one of the best snack places that I have known.

The pics include review for

Potato wedges - love them
Arabbiata pizza - was alright
Chicken BBQ sandwich- must try
Zaatar pide ( beauty..damn delicious upset that isn't back on the menu yet. It was one of my favourites in the city...a must add on every order here)
Cold coffee ( ask to make it strong) and it's thicker than the other known shakes out there.

Please bring the zaatar pide back ♥️

reviews.snippet: A small quaint cafe in Banjara hills. We walked in pretty late for Hyderabad City standards. But the place had a good vibe and the food was also very tasty. We had wraps and one of their signature dishes which is not on their menu card. They have a lot of other items which are not mentioned in the menu so pls do enquire about it before ordering. We had asked them to suggest some dishes to us. They also served us their fresh made chocolate donut as a complimentary sweet diah. It was really well made. Overall a good experience.

reviews.snippet: Been visiting this place since its inception during our college days, It was our college hangout spot as this place serves food which is VFM and of excellent quality. Over the years they have expanded to two new branches nearby and extended the seating area of this place. If you are visiting this place do try the Reshmi Kebab w Cheese Naan also while ordering mention that you want the kebab wrapped in egg fluff. If you are roll lover try the Sheesh tawook roll and chicken zinger roll on the milkshake side I'd recommend their signature Rose Mango milkshake and Pina colada mention that you'd prefer less ice in milkshake.
